The paper presents new techniques for automatically constructing probabilistic programs for data analysis, interpretation, and prediction using Bayesian inference. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG), which are both concerned with probabilistic modeling and inference. The paper also involves the use of domain-specific languages for data modeling, which could place it in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper applies the techniques to time series data and multivariate tabular data, which could place it in the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the synthesis of probabilistic programs for control and prediction, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
